<b><center>Using AND Operator to Convert Lower Case to Upper Case</center></b><font size="--">
<P>
The ASCII codes for :-
<P>
<center>a = 97(decimal) = 61 (hexadecimal)</center>
<P>
<center>A = 65(decimal) = 41 (hexadecimal)</center>
<P>
This differential between lower and upper case letters is maintained for all letters.
<P>
To convert lower case we use the number 5F (hexadecimal) together with the AND operator.
